== Languages ==
In most cases, the name of a language will be the name of the country where it is spoken with the suffix "{{furi|語|ご}}". Example: "France/French" becomes "フランス/フランス語". There are exceptions to these and they are so noted in the country names below.

English is spoken in several countries. These are all called {{furi|英語|えいご}} except in the case of the United States, the language of which is sometimes referred to as {{furi|米語|べいご}}.

== Nationalities ==
The nationality of a person from a particular country is generally that of the country appended with "{{furi|人|じん}}. For example: A Chinese person is "{{furi|中国|ちゅうごく}}{{furi|人|じん}} and a Canadian would be カナダ{{furi|人|じん}}.

