[[Subject:IB Diploma Programme]]

Welcome IB Diploma students!

This will be the main page for study guides, education resources and revision notes created for the [[wikipedia:International Baccalaureate|International Baccalaureate]] Diploma (IBDP) on [[Wikibooks portal|Wikibooks]]. Find out more about the program from the [http://www.ibo.org IB Organization]. If you want, [[Wikibooks:Welcome, newcomers|find out about Wikibooks]].

The aim is to collaborate to create a great resource for IBDP students and teachers to make their learning, study and teaching easier. There are many things to be done and everyone can contribute using the "Edit this page" button at the top of the pages.

* To quickly become useful, we are making a compendium of the best sites on the internet with IBDP resources. This is available at the bottom of this page. If you already use a good site, go to 'edit this page' and share it with everyone by adding it to the list! You can use these pages as a starting point for creating your own notes to contribute (they provide headings to work under) but don't copy copyrighted material.

* Begin writing pages for the IBDP subjects you know about. Write what you feel will help other students. There is no need to be perfect or comprehensive, notes can be built on and revised many times by many people. Go through your own notes or textbook and for each chapter add concise notes on concepts that need to be understood. Use headings or numbers as from your textbook or syllabus outline from the websites listed below.

== IBDP Subjects on Wikibooks ==
Click on these links and then refer to your notes or text book and start writing! Writing concise and good explanations is a way of studying for your exams. 

